    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1891-12-07T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1891-12-07T00:00:00-05:00" n="468" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d468">
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Sir <persName type="from">Julian
                                    Pauncefote</persName> to Mr. <persName type="to">Blaine</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1891-12-07">
                            <hi rend="italic">December 7,
                                1891</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: With reference to previous correspondence
                            on the subject of the disputes in the Apian municipality, and in
                            accordance with instructions which I have received from the Marquis of
                            Salisbury, I have the honor to inform you that Mr. Cusack-Smith, Her
                            Majesty’s consul at Apia, has been instructed by Her Majesty’s
                            Government to continue to pay taxes, etc., as heretofore,
                            notwithstanding the refusal of the chief justice to do so.</p>
                <p>I have, etc.,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Julian
                            Pauncefote.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
